<h2 id="understanding-the-data">Understanding the data</h2>
<h3 id="reviews">Reviews:</h3>
<p>There are 7 columns in this dataset:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>id:</strong> unique identifier and can be used to match with the listing id.</li>
  <li><strong>author:</strong> name of the person who wrote the id. (For this analysis it is irrelevant)</li>
  <li><strong>rating:</strong> from 1 to 5, it can be good to compare it with the results obtained form the sentiment analysis.</li>
  <li><strong>comments:</strong> long strings of text. Could be used for sentiment analysis, finding the most frequent word used etc.</li>
  <li><strong>Polarity:</strong> ranges from -1 to 1. Negative values are considered bad, and positive values good.</li>
  <li><strong>Sentiment:</strong> based on polarity but expressed in words. Negative, Neutral, Positive.</li>
  <li><strong>Keywords_reviews:</strong> this column won’t be used in this analysis.</li>
</ol>

